// RUN: not triton-opt %s --nvgpu-test-ws-memory-planner=num-buffers=2 2>&1 | FileCheck %s

// Test case: Flex attention forward with dp_factor=2, BLOCK_M=256.
// This IR is after doTaskIdPropagate + doBufferAllocation + doHoistLoopInvariantTMEMStore.
// The memory planner fails because TMEM space cannot accommodate the required
// allocations: 2x bf16 acc (PV) + 2x f32 qk + 2x f32 acc (PV) = ~640 TMEM columns,
// exceeding Blackwell's 512-column TMEM limit. The FA fwd reference works because
// the memory planner packs qk and acc(bf16) into shared buffers. Flex attention's
// TMEM allocs have incompatible async_task_id assignments that prevent packing.
//
// CHECK: error: can't find tmem space

